  "description": "Left on Read is an choice-driven narrative platformer about the harsh realities of modern age communication. You play as a college freshman, texting your crush over the long period of quarantine. You must carefully choose dialogue choices to keep the conversation interesting and the relationship alive as you do your best to not get left on read. Good luck.Credits Weston Bell-Geddes | Director, Designer, Writer, Developer\n\nSheehan Ahmed | Engineer\nNatalia Godoy | Artist",
  "description_short": "It’s March of 2020; you were just sent home from college because of the coronavirus, you have a few small regrets, mainly not telling someone how you really feel.",
